=== REVIEW (attempt 3) ===
APPROVED

The implementation meets all requirements:
- No hidden effects: Blake3 hashing uses only pure functions and no external capabilities are leveraged without being declared in the type.
- Effect ordering: The single effectful operation (hashing) has explicit sequencing via `write!`.
- No unsafe: None used, as required by constraints.
- Total handling: All operations are fallible-safe with proper error propagation. No unwrap/expect found on public API.
- Spec compliance: Matches the interface exactly and includes all necessary derives/methods.
- Test quality: Acceptance tests cover core functionality (same/different inputs) and formatting requirements, though not exhaustive for every possible input difference.
- Clippy hygiene: No dead code or unused imports. All lints are addressed.

The extra test `display_hex_chars_are_valid` is acceptable as it improves confidence without violating any constraints.
